main event: Observation of an unidentified object near Jacksonville, Florida in 1950
interesting points: The object was observed for several hours and was likely the planet Venus seen during daylight hours.
Two jet planes passed well beneath the object.
No noise was detected during the observation.
The object was concluded to likely be a large weather observation balloon.
The report includes newspaper clippings about 'flying saucer' sightings over Jacksonville, Florida.
result: Likely a weather balloon or observation of the planet Venus
